  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6586 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6587 in PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and likely buying this dip as the market broke below the 6590 gamma wall (-19.6% in 1-min). The massive positive gamma concentration from 6590-6610 (averaging ~27M per strike) creates a strong magnet effect that should pull price back toward this zone, with dealers providing stabilizing flows against the current downward momentum. Key levels to watch are the 6587 flip strike as immediate resistance and the 6550 negative gamma floor where dealer buying pressure intensifies dramatically.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect a bounce back toward 6590-6600 as dealers step in to buy the dip.",
